This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it discusses the design of social robots that can interact with humans. It also involves the interpretation of gestures produced by an anthropomorphic robot, which falls under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms to recognize these gestures may also place it under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the study involves analyzing video data, which could fall under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category due to the use of machine learning algorithms.
